{
    "title": "Reconstructing Evolution of Knowledge Based on Representation of Academic Research Papers",
    "authors": [
        "Shihyu Chang",
        "Yi-Jun Wu",
        "Mao-Shuen Lee"
    ],
    "abstract": "There has been an explosion of academic research in various fields over the past decades, which can be highly complex and interdisciplinary. Although numerous works have been conducted to analyze the evolution of academic research, existing methods are limited in their ability to provide a global overview of the dynamics. In this paper, we propose a data-driven approach to reconstruct the evolution of knowledge based on the representation of academic research papers. We first construct a citation network to represent the relationships between papers. Then, through a dimensionality reduction technique, we transform the high-dimensional representation of papers into a low-dimensional space, in which the trajectories of papers' knowledge discovery can be visualized. By exploiting the temporal information of papers' citing and being cited behaviors, we are able to capture the dynamics of knowledge exploration within all papers. Through case studies and quantitative evaluation on a real-world dataset, we demonstrate the effectiveness of our method for reconstructing the evolution of knowledge.", 
}
